                        .col-xl-4.col-lg-5
                            .featured-text.text-center.text-lg-left
                                h4 Paintings on Canvas
                                p.mb-0
                                    | &quot;I use oil paint to express my experience of Knapdale. The paintings are often abstract and non-representational, 
                                    | sometimes with visual anchors of sea, sky or land, to offer the viewer the opportunity to reconnect with their own emotional memories of being in nature. 
                                    | Through the work I am aiming to find a visual language using colour and mark-making which conveys the particular elemental beauty and quality of light in this corner of Argyll.&quot;
                    
